53	\N	a sanjaya season: technically, it's not over, but c'mon, it's over.	<p>i'm sure what will be going through sanjaya's mind when he eventually gets voted off is what it would be like if he were being judged on different criteria other than the criteria he's actually being judged on -- singing.  fortunately, in oz, you can.  you can see how well your bracket would've done if we were using scoring systems of some other sites.  go to the <a href="http://ordinaryzelig.org/pool/standings">standings</a>, change the scoring system, and dream on.  (if you know of any scoring systems that you'd like to simulate, let me know.)</p>\n\n<p>now that you've seen the results, i'd like to present the very first annual sanjaya malakar award to john meyer, aka JoJoMe.  yes, you did well in the other systems, but they don't count.  maybe next year the sanjaya award recipient will get their money back.  but probably not.  congratulations.  it's ironic that you won this award when it clearly should've gone to stephanie, but hey, we're obviously not judging on hair.  and before you give me the william hung award, i'd like to say that that is just mean and racist.</p>\n\n<p>my scoring system obviously rewards players who correctly pick upsets if they happen.  someone asked me to see how a bracket would do if it were composed of only upsets (naturally this request came from a person who was at the bottom of the standings 2 years in a row), so i did.</p>\n\n<p>this year, all upsets would result in only 5 correct pics, all in the first round, totalling only 49 points.  but this year upsets were sparse.</p>\n\n<p>last year, however, picking all upsets would result in 10 correct pics totalling 128 points.  the only upset that wasn't in the first round was bradley.  interestingly enough, picking all upsets wouldn't have even gotten last place:  2 people did worse than that.  what's funny is that the <strong style="font-size: 125%;">adler women</strong> were those 2.  yes, this year paints quite a different picture, but theoretically, if someone had picked only upsets in the first round, picked bradley, and then just quit, that would have been enough to beat the adler women.  almost as embarrassing as getting beat by them, ever.</p>\n\n<p>i'm open to discussion on scoring systems, suggestions, criticisms, etc.  as a cubs fan, i've already started thinking about next year.</p>\n\n<h2>thanks for playing everybody.</h2>	2	2007-04-01 19:23:34+00
